# JavaScript Basics

# Project Overview
This project demonstrates basic JavaScript concepts with a modern and futuristic user interface.  
It includes alert messages, dynamic text changes, form validation, and a simple calculator.

# Objectives Covered
- Alert on button click
- Change text dynamically
- Perform calculator operations
- Validate form inputs
- Display validation messages

# Features
- Animated gradient background
- Glass-style user interface
- Styled buttons with hover effects
- Real-time validation feedback
- Interactive calculator

# Files Included
- index.html – Structure and UI design
- script.js – JavaScript functionality
- README.md – Project documentation

# JavaScript Concepts Used
- Functions
- DOM manipulation
- Event handling
- Conditional statements
- Form validation logic
- parseFloat and isNaN for calculations

# How to Run
1. Keep index.html and script.js in the same folder.
2. Open index.html in a web browser.
3. Interact with buttons, calculator, and form fields.

# Author
Created as part of Day 6 JavaScript Basics learning task.